[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Troubleshooting Gradle issues**\n\nI see that native image compilation is failing because gradleTestKit is dragging in Gradle API 9.1 with service providers. I’m wondering if we should avoid gradleTestKit altogether and think about instantiating ProGuardTask instead, but that might require some Gradle internals. It seems like using ProjectBuilder from the Gradle core could help avoid issues, but I'm skeptical since the DefaultTask constructor might throw if not created by Gradle itself. I'll have to inspect that further, especially since tests mainly use public methods.\n\n**Exploring Gradle compilation**\n\nThe developer mentioned not to compile or run tests, but I think we can utilize `javap` instead. I’m considering avoiding ProjectBuilder by using Unsafe, although direct reflection is restricted in tests. We need to stick to the public API, so I’m questioning if using the ProGuardTask constructor qualifies as that. If DefaultTask prohibits it, that could complicate things. I might modify the tests to handle GradleException. Exploring with `javap` for the DefaultTask constructor might help us understand more without needing Gradle itself.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b261ae36c6e8a600169fe03f768008196a1f9188b3d00871d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_gP_qEglW6cGlEya26VgpEMdEG6RB9a2d3mM1Gnwjhd04p3UyZH0aH9-av3_kuTPvnsy4c-PLxUEHxDEeZJj5VSWBx4RGMRNxHTv3sa9MUFXrhwz_y1sx1XajkbsTHXHeEi7rjRCalZbyWhXsZvo4_2J3idpQNXK0WSd-HJCulMPjwsaiRc1fJkGQOempjKJFKIfWsl3xuHp3vBoh-Xgph-OJbR3b_QaMtexXpbVhpj6lkxmXXPNU_epm3U1h1f9a36clH1MAjZDFQQBlY0azw-3KuauZTuebx9bNeojia84sKKlxCzThqLGTTwJlPKe64ZJQ7wP3-FSTXWSgTf16JNlqagCoRF8d3bZoxS3fDs8ejCZfUSln7zcdljtAUobCyIZxwYFQaGe1N-pTILHW2hdwx7NRnY_QUKqrohzOq5FXm9pZEnyBtZOqn4_SZzp3uwhISezjvae5hMCOGa06K6dAxY_8YCwqAKUxPjTiaand3-7GZ11lgid82oQ7noZJwfXMY0p5dYWRe9EMNnBr43S9LjNh_2smHiw_-8aNXaJYejQtZEUPcMtruv9dRTRsALXgpQv0n